-- Lampard Suffers Thigh Injury in England Training, Will Have Scan
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-05-30T12:49:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-30/lampard-suffers-thigh-injury-in-england-training-will-have-scan.html
England midfielder  Frank Lampard  will
undergo a scan after suffering a thigh injury in training today,
the Football Association said on its website.  Chelsea’s Lampard will be examined by England’s medical
team tomorrow, the F.A. said. Liverpool’s Jordan Henderson has
been put on standby notice for the England squad while Lampard
continues to be monitored.  England opens play as soccer’s 2012 European Championship
against France on June 11.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  